WEBVTT

1
00:00:27.365 --> 00:00:29.005
It's going to burn. Flip it.

2
00:00:35.446 --> 00:00:37.046
What time is her bus?

3
00:00:38.446 --> 00:00:39.675
7pm.

4
00:00:41.145 --> 00:00:42.315
She must be on it now.

5
00:00:44.986 --> 00:00:47.186
Is Ji Ho immigrating to Europe?

6
00:00:47.486 --> 00:00:49.126
What's the fuss about her going back home?

7
00:00:49.556 --> 00:00:52.796
It takes 4 hours to Namhae and 3 hours if we drive fast.

8
00:00:53.326 --> 00:00:54.796
It's not that.

9
00:00:55.425 --> 00:00:58.135
It was really hard for Ji Ho to move to Seoul.

10
00:00:58.395 --> 00:01:01.936
She got into university in one go and moved then.

11
00:01:02.065 --> 00:01:04.876
Even if she gets into Harvard, it's no use...

12
00:01:04.975 --> 00:01:07.276
if her parents won't let her go.

13
00:01:08.546 --> 00:01:09.576
Why wouldn't they?

14
00:01:11.445 --> 00:01:13.546
Ji Ho wasn't allowed to go anywhere else...

15
00:01:13.546 --> 00:01:15.615
other than Namhae National University.

16
00:01:15.916 --> 00:01:17.356
Her dad said it costs too much for Seoul.

17
00:01:17.356 --> 00:01:20.115
Really? Then how did she come to Seoul?

18
00:01:21.386 --> 00:01:23.996
The thing is, Ji Ho...

19
00:01:24.425 --> 00:01:26.595
- is a little crazy. - Crazy.

20
00:01:26.626 --> 00:01:29.766
Ji Ho? She's the nicest person I know.

21
00:01:29.996 --> 00:01:32.095
You must not know her yet.

22
00:01:32.666 --> 00:01:34.666
(10 years ago)

23
00:01:34.666 --> 00:01:36.005
This isn't too bad.

24
00:01:36.005 --> 00:01:37.975
Her dad had a philosophy.

25
00:01:38.335 --> 00:01:40.076
If she can't become a judge or a prosecutor,

26
00:01:40.076 --> 00:01:42.005
the only other option was becoming a teacher.

27
00:01:42.675 --> 00:01:46.115
But her marks weren't good enough for Seoul National University law.

28
00:01:52.686 --> 00:01:55.055
(Seoul National University, College of Law)

29
00:01:58.695 --> 00:02:01.095
Her dream was to become a writer since she was young.

30
00:02:01.326 --> 00:02:03.496
That's why she decided to try for Korean literature.

31
00:02:06.496 --> 00:02:10.305
That's why she brought it up while having dinner.

32
00:02:10.905 --> 00:02:11.976
Dad.

33
00:02:12.476 --> 00:02:14.546
I want to study Korean...

34
00:02:14.606 --> 00:02:16.576
What?

35
00:02:17.775 --> 00:02:20.745
Her dad flipped over the table.

36
00:02:20.946 --> 00:02:23.546
No way. How did she persuade him?

37
00:02:23.546 --> 00:02:24.786
Persuade him?

38
00:02:24.916 --> 00:02:26.925
I told you, she's crazy.

39
00:02:30.055 --> 00:02:32.655
She registered herself without anyone knowing.

40
00:02:32.756 --> 00:02:34.266
The day before the first day,

41
00:02:35.726 --> 00:02:37.935
(Namhae to Seoul)

42
00:02:38.566 --> 00:02:40.036
she ran away from home at night.

43
00:02:43.506 --> 00:02:44.976
(Namhae National University of Education)

44
00:02:51.576 --> 00:02:52.976
Okay, bye.

45
00:02:56.346 --> 00:02:57.916
(Where are you? I'm in front of your school. Come out.)

46
00:03:08.826 --> 00:03:11.236
Until she finished her first semester,

47
00:03:11.236 --> 00:03:13.196
her dad thought Ji Ho was attending Namhae University.

48
00:03:14.736 --> 00:03:16.435
She really is crazy.

49
00:03:17.775 --> 00:03:19.736
I thought Soo Ji was the crazy one.

50
00:03:19.736 --> 00:03:22.606
No, Soo Ji just has a bad personality.

51
00:03:23.615 --> 00:03:24.816
Ji Ho...

52
00:03:25.245 --> 00:03:28.386
always surprises you at the most unexpected times.

53
00:03:32.856 --> 00:03:35.625
The driver won't wait long because he's upset.

54
00:03:35.826 --> 00:03:37.395
So give me a quick answer.

55
00:03:38.096 --> 00:03:39.196
Okay.

56
00:03:39.296 --> 00:03:40.666
Will you...

57
00:03:41.326 --> 00:03:42.525
marry me?

58
00:03:45.335 --> 00:03:48.106
Hurry. He's waiting.

59
00:03:50.136 --> 00:03:51.205
Okay.

60
00:03:51.536 --> 00:03:53.705
Then I'll go unload my luggage.

61
00:03:54.106 --> 00:03:56.006
He's very upset.

62
00:03:57.245 --> 00:03:58.346
Look.

63
00:04:00.346 --> 00:04:02.085
I have something to ask before then.

64
00:04:02.245 --> 00:04:03.786
Go ahead.

65
00:04:04.155 --> 00:04:05.386
By any chance,

66
00:04:09.356 --> 00:04:10.726
do you like me?

67
00:04:14.196 --> 00:04:15.266
No.

68
00:04:16.125 --> 00:04:18.296
Bring out your stuff. I'll wait inside.

69
00:04:38.385 --> 00:04:41.956
I noticed that you washed the instant noodle bowl.

70
00:04:43.656 --> 00:04:45.596
Yes, it's a habit.

71
00:04:46.726 --> 00:04:49.695
You have a really good habit.

72
00:04:50.865 --> 00:04:52.096
Thank you.

73
00:04:53.805 --> 00:04:55.765
- There's a seat. Sit down. - No, you sit.

74
00:04:55.765 --> 00:04:57.005
It's okay, you sit.

75
00:04:57.836 --> 00:04:58.875
Give me your bag.

76
00:04:59.606 --> 00:05:01.805
- Your hair looks good. - Doesn't it?

77
00:05:02.305 --> 00:05:03.875
- I'm hot. - Are you?

78
00:05:09.385 --> 00:05:10.555
You should sit.

79
00:05:11.115 --> 00:05:12.755
You can sit first.

80
00:05:12.856 --> 00:05:13.986
That's okay.

81
00:05:42.745 --> 00:05:44.015
I'm on my way...

82
00:05:45.286 --> 00:05:48.425
to get married to my landlord.

83
00:05:59.736 --> 00:06:01.606
My conditions haven't changed.

84
00:06:02.906 --> 00:06:04.276
Do you have any objections?

85
00:06:07.646 --> 00:06:11.015
No, not to your conditions.

86
00:06:12.875 --> 00:06:16.146
Is there something you want to add?

87
00:06:18.185 --> 00:06:21.986
As you know, I had to quit work.

88
00:06:23.356 --> 00:06:25.596
Until I find a new job,

89
00:06:27.166 --> 00:06:30.026
I need some adjustment to the rent.

90
00:06:32.466 --> 00:06:35.736
Would you be able to lower the rent?

91
00:06:36.635 --> 00:06:38.675
How much were you thinking?

92
00:06:40.846 --> 00:06:42.075
About 50 dollars.

93
00:06:43.075 --> 00:06:44.646
If you could give me the discount,

94
00:06:45.346 --> 00:06:47.815
it wouldn't be too much for me.

95
00:06:54.026 --> 00:06:56.185
Okay. Let's do that.

96
00:06:57.026 --> 00:07:00.325
We'll make our contract 250 dollars a month.

97
00:07:00.666 --> 00:07:03.226
Okay. Thank you.

98
00:07:05.765 --> 00:07:07.406
Are you sure you can handle it?

99
00:07:10.606 --> 00:07:11.706
I'm talking about the marriage.

100
00:07:13.646 --> 00:07:16.305
It might be more economical at this state...

101
00:07:16.445 --> 00:07:18.315
to go back home.

102
00:07:20.716 --> 00:07:21.885
No.

103
00:07:23.346 --> 00:07:26.925
Even if I go back, I still have to find a job.

104
00:07:28.456 --> 00:07:32.656
On top of that, I'll have conflicts with Dad.

105
00:07:34.226 --> 00:07:36.296
The only difference would be the rent.

106
00:07:37.135 --> 00:07:39.995
There wouldn't be anything better than Seoul.

107
00:07:40.836 --> 00:07:42.305
There are no jobs either.

108
00:07:44.276 --> 00:07:46.945
It looks like the stress level is beyond the rental fee.

109
00:07:48.675 --> 00:07:50.916
However, I was surprised.

110
00:07:52.115 --> 00:07:55.615
I thought you considered marriages to be based on love.

111
00:07:56.385 --> 00:07:58.755
It was very unexpected...

112
00:07:59.055 --> 00:08:02.086
when you chose this marriage based on tenancy.

113
00:08:03.486 --> 00:08:04.695
Well...

114
00:08:05.796 --> 00:08:07.565
Just like you said,

115
00:08:08.765 --> 00:08:12.666
love and affection...

116
00:08:15.565 --> 00:08:18.375
aren't something I need for at least two years.

117
00:08:19.805 --> 00:08:23.505
What I need right now is that room.

118
00:08:25.445 --> 00:08:27.815
I decided to marry my tenant today.

119
00:08:29.515 --> 00:08:30.656
I know.

120
00:08:31.755 --> 00:08:34.726
It's not a choice an ordinary person would make.

121
00:08:37.295 --> 00:08:38.655
To be honest,

122
00:08:41.566 --> 00:08:43.295
I really wanted...

123
00:08:45.365 --> 00:08:46.836
to try it once.

124
00:08:48.905 --> 00:08:50.005
Marriage.

125
00:08:51.106 --> 00:08:52.905
I found...

126
00:08:55.676 --> 00:08:57.375
Did you sort the recycling this week?

127
00:08:59.275 --> 00:09:01.216
a very unusual woman as my wife.

128
00:09:04.915 --> 00:09:08.486
(Episode 4: Because This Is My First Marriage)

129
00:09:31.115 --> 00:09:32.446
I...

130
00:09:34.245 --> 00:09:35.645
slept so well.

131
00:10:09.446 --> 00:10:10.915
Good morning.

132
00:10:11.385 --> 00:10:12.486
Hello.

133
00:10:16.556 --> 00:10:18.155
Do you want some?

134
00:10:18.395 --> 00:10:21.265
I made a little too much for breakfast.

135
00:10:21.265 --> 00:10:25.295
I'm okay. A cup of americano is good enough for breakfast.

136
00:10:26.336 --> 00:10:27.466
Okay.

137
00:10:54.295 --> 00:10:55.525
It's so delicious.

138
00:10:55.966 --> 00:10:57.995
The food and the night too.

139
00:10:58.395 --> 00:11:01.736
I haven't had such a sweet morning in a long time.

140
00:11:02.336 --> 00:11:03.976
It's just as the saying goes.

141
00:11:04.635 --> 00:11:06.736
I can hardly support myself.

142
00:11:07.005 --> 00:11:09.775
How can I date and love in this state?

143
00:11:10.245 --> 00:11:12.346
I don't even have 5,000 dollars for a deposit.

144
00:11:12.446 --> 00:11:15.415
Thanks to this marriage, I got a 50-dollar discount.

145
00:11:15.486 --> 00:11:17.785
How much would that amount to in two years?

146
00:11:20.785 --> 00:11:23.226
What a great choice, Ji Ho.

147
00:11:26.495 --> 00:11:29.596
I feel so comfortable. Both Kitty and I.

148
00:11:30.795 --> 00:11:33.135
It's been so long since I had such a peaceful weekend.

149
00:11:35.336 --> 00:11:37.635
I don't have to suffer through blind dates...

150
00:11:38.436 --> 00:11:40.905
and get stressed about recycling.

151
00:11:41.806 --> 00:11:45.076
By giving a 50-dollar discount, I gained such a valuable serenity.

152
00:11:47.415 --> 00:11:49.946
I used an egg.

153
00:11:49.946 --> 00:11:51.456
I'll refill it later.

154
00:11:52.216 --> 00:11:53.316
Okay.

155
00:12:06.535 --> 00:12:10.535
Yes. Marrying my tenant was the answer.

156
00:12:14.176 --> 00:12:15.476
Yes, it's me.

157
00:12:16.706 --> 00:12:18.816
What? Was that today?

158
00:12:19.576 --> 00:12:21.946
Oh. Okay.

159
00:12:22.346 --> 00:12:24.155
I'll come this evening.

160
00:12:24.515 --> 00:12:26.885
Okay. Have a safe trip.

161
00:12:27.285 --> 00:12:28.385
Okay.

162
00:12:29.385 --> 00:12:30.795
Is it your parents?

163
00:12:31.125 --> 00:12:35.696
Yes. There is a wedding, so they're coming to Seoul.

164
00:12:36.295 --> 00:12:40.135
I think I'll have to go to my brother's tonight.

165
00:12:40.466 --> 00:12:43.165
Then should I come with you?

166
00:12:43.836 --> 00:12:45.976
Pardon? Why?

167
00:12:46.206 --> 00:12:48.976
If we're getting married, I should say hello.

168
00:12:50.816 --> 00:12:51.946
That's true.

169
00:12:52.216 --> 00:12:54.885
We should do those things if we're getting married.

170
00:12:55.045 --> 00:12:59.086
Yes. I arranged the process last night.

171
00:12:59.586 --> 00:13:00.856
Okay.

172
00:13:01.186 --> 00:13:02.356
(Process for two-year tenancy marriage)

173
00:13:02.356 --> 00:13:03.525
(Wedding process)

174
00:13:03.525 --> 00:13:06.426
(Meet the parents, wedding hall, dress, photoshoot, honeymoon...)

175
00:13:08.995 --> 00:13:12.736
Are we doing all of that?

176
00:13:13.035 --> 00:13:14.905
What you see now is an ordinary wedding.

177
00:13:14.905 --> 00:13:17.505
If it's a wedding based on love,

178
00:13:17.505 --> 00:13:19.436
these are the procedures one must go through.

179
00:13:19.576 --> 00:13:22.375
As for us, we can skip it all.

180
00:13:23.915 --> 00:13:27.186
We just need to focus on this. That's all we need to do.

181
00:13:27.186 --> 00:13:32.115
Okay. Will you come today then?

182
00:13:32.415 --> 00:13:34.726
I think that would be efficient.

183
00:13:35.326 --> 00:13:37.096
If it's too sudden...

184
00:13:37.826 --> 00:13:40.326
No, let's go today.

185
00:13:41.495 --> 00:13:42.596
Okay.

186
00:13:46.035 --> 00:13:48.005
- Goodbye. - Bye.

187
00:13:52.576 --> 00:13:54.806
- Seul Gi. - Yes?

188
00:13:55.145 --> 00:13:57.476
You took the wrong order down for table 13, didn't you?

189
00:13:57.476 --> 00:13:59.216
Yes, I did.

190
00:13:59.716 --> 00:14:02.285
I'm sorry. I won't make the same mistake.

191
00:14:02.785 --> 00:14:04.356
That's impossible.

192
00:14:04.785 --> 00:14:05.885
Pardon?

193
00:14:05.885 --> 00:14:07.726
Of course you'll make mistakes when you're training.

194
00:14:07.986 --> 00:14:10.956
Just tell me when you do, so I can take care of it.

195
00:14:11.826 --> 00:14:13.056
Yes, ma'am.

196
00:14:13.795 --> 00:14:15.826
There's a reservation on table three, so go set it up.

197
00:14:15.826 --> 00:14:16.936
Okay.

198
00:14:28.576 --> 00:14:30.775
What's this? You didn't tell me.

199
00:14:30.846 --> 00:14:32.245
I'm going to get mad at you.

200
00:14:32.375 --> 00:14:34.915
We had five bottles of makgeolli last night because of you.

201
00:14:34.915 --> 00:14:37.015
That's why I came right away.

202
00:14:38.655 --> 00:14:41.326
So? Are you moving back in as housemates?

203
00:14:41.785 --> 00:14:44.525
Yes, we're like housemates, but...

204
00:14:45.696 --> 00:14:47.125
It's a long story.

205
00:14:47.125 --> 00:14:49.125
The three of us should meet.

206
00:14:49.326 --> 00:14:51.096
Did you tell Soo Ji? What did she say?

207
00:14:51.096 --> 00:14:55.306
I called her. She told me we should just drink.

208
00:14:55.765 --> 00:14:57.905
She can drink more after that?

209
00:14:58.505 --> 00:15:01.245
Is she a rabbit? She must have spare lungs.

210
00:15:03.446 --> 00:15:05.846
What is that? Meat? Beef?

211
00:15:05.846 --> 00:15:08.316
This? I have to go somewhere after.

212
00:15:08.816 --> 00:15:11.885
Now that I look at it, you look different today.

213
00:15:12.285 --> 00:15:15.456
You even have a bag.

214
00:15:17.596 --> 00:15:18.795
What is this?

215
00:15:19.056 --> 00:15:23.966
You look like you're going to meet someone important.

216
00:15:27.035 --> 00:15:28.165
Ji Ho.

217
00:15:28.865 --> 00:15:29.966
What?

218
00:15:30.535 --> 00:15:32.236
Are you meeting a new writer?

219
00:15:32.976 --> 00:15:34.076
Yes.

220
00:15:34.476 --> 00:15:36.275
Great idea.

221
00:15:36.275 --> 00:15:38.115
There are many writers in the world.

222
00:15:38.115 --> 00:15:40.285
It'd be a waste for you to quit because of them.

223
00:15:45.285 --> 00:15:47.885
Ho Rang. I have a question to ask you.

224
00:15:47.885 --> 00:15:48.986
What?

225
00:15:50.895 --> 00:15:54.895
When a guy is meeting a girl's parents,

226
00:15:56.865 --> 00:16:00.306
what should the guy say to impress the parents?

227
00:16:00.606 --> 00:16:05.106
Like... If he was trying to get their permission for marriage.

228
00:16:06.236 --> 00:16:07.645
Why do you want to know that?

229
00:16:09.275 --> 00:16:10.946
Well...

230
00:16:12.645 --> 00:16:14.115
Is it for a line in the drama?

231
00:16:15.186 --> 00:16:16.586
Is the new writer testing you?

232
00:16:16.686 --> 00:16:19.015
I'm the expert in stuff like this.

233
00:16:19.115 --> 00:16:20.155
I know, right?

234
00:17:04.466 --> 00:17:05.595
You arrived early.

235
00:17:05.995 --> 00:17:07.065
Yes.

236
00:17:11.775 --> 00:17:13.646
The bus is coming. Shall we go?

237
00:17:13.646 --> 00:17:14.676
Okay.

238
00:17:30.696 --> 00:17:32.855
Will there be any other issues that I should be aware of...

239
00:17:33.126 --> 00:17:35.196
other than those three?

240
00:17:36.626 --> 00:17:38.535
There's one variable.

241
00:17:38.835 --> 00:17:41.666
My younger brother can get a bit out of control.

242
00:17:41.835 --> 00:17:44.236
What do you mean, out of control?

243
00:17:46.206 --> 00:17:48.805
Never mind. I'll take care of him, so don't worry.

244
00:17:49.176 --> 00:17:52.916
You just need to be careful in talking to my dad.

245
00:17:53.376 --> 00:17:56.785
Okay. I'll keep those three ways in mind.

246
00:17:57.686 --> 00:17:58.916
If...

247
00:17:59.156 --> 00:18:01.456
all the three ways don't work out,

248
00:18:01.825 --> 00:18:05.456
you'll have to use another means.

249
00:18:05.495 --> 00:18:07.666
And what is that?

250
00:18:07.726 --> 00:18:11.535
You might not like this idea.

251
00:18:14.236 --> 00:18:17.075
You know, I got some advice from my friend...

252
00:18:17.406 --> 00:18:19.406
because she's the expert in marriage.

253
00:18:22.105 --> 00:18:24.646
These are the crucial comments to win your father-in-law's favor.

254
00:18:24.946 --> 00:18:28.886
The first one is, "I won't let her do any harsh work in her life."

255
00:18:29.085 --> 00:18:32.886
The second one is, "I'll make sure she becomes a madam."

256
00:18:33.186 --> 00:18:37.055
The third one is, "I'll serve her like a princess all my life."

257
00:18:37.295 --> 00:18:41.196
The fourth one is, "I'll love her until the day I die."

258
00:18:41.966 --> 00:18:44.936
This... This actually works?

259
00:18:45.166 --> 00:18:47.305
Yes, maybe.

260
00:18:47.535 --> 00:18:51.406
No, I'll stop this from happening no matter what.

261
00:19:04.386 --> 00:19:05.456
Ji Ho.

262
00:19:05.656 --> 00:19:07.825
You got so fine after moving out.

263
00:19:08.126 --> 00:19:10.696
- These clothes seem new. - No, they're not.

264
00:19:10.696 --> 00:19:13.866
- I haven't seen this bag either. - Stop it.

265
00:19:13.866 --> 00:19:15.396
I don't think so.

266
00:19:16.265 --> 00:19:18.835
- And a new guy. - Gosh, I've had...

267
00:19:21.406 --> 00:19:25.105
Well, he's my boyfriend. Say hi.

268
00:19:26.035 --> 00:19:28.505
It's nice to meet you. I'm Nam Se Hee.

269
00:19:28.845 --> 00:19:31.176
Hello, I'm Yoon Ji Seok.

